text:
Hello, I am Mekdim, the liason for Whiz Kids Workshop (WKW) to this fantastic group.

WKW is a CSO working to better the future of children in Ethiopia and Africa. We are currently working hard to create awareness about COVID19 in Ethiopia at the request of the Minster of Health, Dr Lia Tadesse.

We are developing original contents in several Ethiopian languages, and dubbing awareness videos prepared in English in Amharic to be distributed in various platforms.

We are also working on the ground by allocating teams in crowded Addis roads and giving out vital information about the prevention methods of COVID19.

In addition, we are preparing a website to share valuable and verified data about the disease. The website will include our awareness creation videos and other necessary information.

We need all the help we can get from people outside Ethiopia as well as people inside

In Addis we are struggling with slow internet connections working from home

By the end of today WKW will have it’s SLACK space set up and our first call out will be for translators and speakers in the following languages. Af-Somali, Haddiyyssa, Wollaaitta, Sdamu-Afoo, and other local languages.

Thank you in advance for your interest in helping out.
